.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-2-6::.
There are 4 different nationalities: canadian, indian, brazilian, japanese
The people use 4 different means of transport: bike, motorbike, skateboard, subway
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: ice-hockey, rowing, soccer, swimming
1. the person driving the subway is on the left of the person who's sport is rowing##1
2. the canadian is on the left of the person who's sport is soccer##1
3. the canadian is on the right of the person who's sport is ice-hockey##1
4. the person who's sport is swimming is on the left of the indian##1
5. the person driving the bike is between the person driving the subway and the person who's sport is soccer##2
6. the indian is between the canadian and the brazilian##2
7. the person who's sport is ice-hockey is on the right of the person driving the skateboard##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1     |     2      |   3    |     4      |
| Nationality    | brazilian | indian  | canadian | japanese      |
| Transport   | skateboard  | subway  | bike | motorbike |
| Sport   | swimming | ice-hockey | rowing | soccer     |

